      • getKeyAliasMap

        protected java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.String> getKeyAliasMap()
        Map the name of field as in form json to the column name of the client object returned after mother lookup For instance you may name your field as Mother_Guardian_First_Name whereas the client object returned uses first_name. So this map will map the field key to the column name. E.g. Mother_Guardian_First_Name -> first_name
        Returns:
        a map of key against their column names.
